==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Affrightment
<hw>Af*fright"ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Affright; the
state of being frightened; sudden fear or alarm.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Passionate words or blows . . . fill the child's mind with terror
and <qex>affrightment</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Affront</ent>⟦br⟧
